This is a review for the IdentoGO services provided inside this H&R Block.

I came here to complete my TSA PreCheck application. The place was empty save for the one guy working here. All the empty cubicles made this place feel like an abandoned building in a ghost town. That's what happens when tax season is over!

I had an appointment, but I could've easily have just walked in. After I signed in, the gentleman took me to the back of the office and seated me in front of a monitor. He went over my information (which was already in the system because I'd entered it when booking my appointment), took my fingerprints digitally (no messy ink!), and took my credit card for payment.

The whole process was extremely efficient and was over in 5 minutes. Seriously, it took me longer to write this review than the amount of time I spent in the H&R Block office!







Lew Lee has been helping me find peace of mind at tax time in recent years.

Friendly help without judgement makes all the difference.







This is also the location for TSA Pre enrollment. I am only commenting on their TSA Pre services. Do NOT, I repeat,  Do NOT show up here without an appt. While walk-ins are supposed to be served when appts. don't show they will do everything possible to not serve a walk-in, even taking appt. holders 10 min. early ahead of a walk-in. It actually reached a point of ridiculousness where the other walk-in and I bet that even though we were the only two in the waiting room, we bet that they still would wait for an appt. to show vs. serve us.







