        3/17/2016
    

Had a 9:00 AM appointment with Bill Chan this morning. He is such a personable fellow, he made the whole nasty, tax paying ordeal, a walk in the park. The lady upfront, seemed to be a little lost, as to what her duties were, not sure if it was her first day, or if she was in training. I let her know I was there, she seemed to try to verify my appointment, then nothing. I just stood there, not knowing if she had finished with me or not. Finally, I just went and sat down, then someone else came out, and let me know my appointment would be in a few minutes. Other, than that, it would've been 5 stars. A humorous side note, the poor receptionist also, had the printer run out of ink on her (tough first morning) and she wasn't sure how to fix it. My girlfriend over heard her dilemma, and when Bill and I came out of the cubicle, my girlfriend was loading the printer ink for the lady. glad she could help and I will definitely use them again. Parking was not to bad.








