        3/26/2015
    

The tax consultant Mindy Szutu was not able to explain any of the decisions she was talking while filing my returns. At the very least, she should have been able to explain why she was using itemized versus standard deductions, but she could not since she was basically trying the brute force method of keying in different combinations into the software to see which combination gave the lowest tax.She was also not able to explain other things like whether we should file jointly since we were married or separately. She came to the conclusion based on 2 reports she ran that we should file separately. However, when cross checking her work ,I realized she had  made an error that would have led me to pay $7000 in excess tax. Also, similar to other peoples experience, the initial estimate was $300-$400, but in the end it became $700 because our returns were"complicated". Both my husband and I have usual bay area type income - salary and stock options from our employers, plus some mutual fund investments. Nothing too complicated, yet they were unable to give us an accurate estimate of the cost of filing a return. I do not see the point of paying $700 for shoddy work where I have no confidence in the decisions made.




