        3/20/2014
    

Never use Annie Jones- she forgot to file our return. I honestly do not think I need to write any more than that because forgetting to file someone's returns equals she doesn't do her job. But here it goes... My husband and I went to H&R Block for the first time- we were loyal Turbotax users. But seeing as we bought a house last year, we gave this a shot. We set up the appointment and went. Annie's demenaor was unemotional, unfriendly, and uncommunicative. She did not explain any part of the process or ramifications. She just put numbers into the computer which spit out how much we owed. When we had questions, she was unable to answer them intelligently or give us any kind of remedial suggestions for next year. I asked her up front how much the services would cost and she quoted us about $200. It turned out to be $350. We paid it reluctantly- and said- whatever, our taxes are done. Or so we thought. On taxes, you can choose the date that the gov't removes the owed funds. We chose 2 weeks from when we met with Annie. That day came and went and nothing was deducted. I thought that odd because at the end of the day, it's the feds. They need their money. So i gave it a few more days and still no withdrawal. So I called the office and asked about it. I was met with a highly unintelligent, very difficult to understand women on the other end of the phone that could not understand my question. Once we finally gained comprehension at a 1st grad level- they said, oh that date is arbitrary, don't worry the gov't will take out their money. I laughed and said- well then don't give people the option to set the date- just tell them it will be taken out when the gov't gets around to it. I then went home  a little skeptical and looked up on the H&R Block website the status of our filing- it came up with "no information". That again raised red flags. I called the office again and got a new lady, much more helpful and intelligent. She looked up my info and thought that was odd so she promised to call me back. No call was returned. The next morning- blood beginning to boil- i checked online again. The status now said our return was rejected by the IRS. Neat.I called the customer service line which they recommended doing which had no more information and told me to call the office that had filed to work with them. Here we go again. I called, same unintelligible woman answers- I ask to speak to someone else or a manager- she refuses. So I try to once again explain the situation- and she says "OH- I filed your return last night". I am sorry, what? You filed my returns only after I reminded you that they were not filed? You filed them in a hurry because the client called you and told you to do your job? Cool. She then told me she was with someone and would have to call me back. I told her that I had some serious questions for her but she refused to answer them and told me she would call me back. I said fine and hung up. No call was returned. I finally call back- get the nice lady again. She said that my tax preparer was going to call me back in 5 minutes. Nope, she didn't. So I went over there- to see this through in person. I get there and my tax preparer is getting water and chatting it up with the receptionist. She sees me and gets uncomfortable. I grabbed a tootsie roll from the bowl and sit down in her office. She explains that she wasn't in yesterday and that's why there was no call back- but our taxes are filed and received by the gov't. She said she forgot to follow up with her manager to get it approved before sending it in and that's why they weren't filed until now. I explained how unacceptable that was and how that is not doing her job. I told her that I shouldn't have to prompt her to do her job. It is my taxes- my life- my money. She needs to be respectful of that. She didn't get it- no affect- no apology. I asked her what remedy I could get for this oversight. She forwarded me to her manager- who I intend to follow up with for a major complaint and requesting a discount. This is NOT the service I am paying for. I could have done our taxes with Turbotax and trusted that it was filed. Instead, I left this responsibility in Annie's hands- and she failed.




